( Since this question is specific to BIND, it would have been better
  suited to the BIND mailing list... &lt;bind@ucbarpa.berkeley.edu&gt; )

It is dubious whether the nameserver is an appropriate place to do this --
I doubt very much if it is...

A more appropriate solution would be to fix the terminal server.  Have it
listen to rwho packets (yetch!) and cache the load factor information that
is included.  Then, pick the one with the lowest load.  Of course, the
information will always be somewhat stale.

To be really thorough, the terminal server could send systat requests to
the 5 least loaded hosts to make the finalizing pick.

-Philip

